<item>
            <title>[HBASE-394] [hbase] Updating a row on non-existent table runs all the retries and timeouts instead of failing fast</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-394</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you try to access row in non-existent table, the client hangs waiting on all timeouts and retries.  Rather it should be able to fail fast if no such table.&lt;/p&gt;







</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12383042">HBASE-394</key>
            <summary>[hbase] Updating a row on non-existent table runs all the retries and timeouts instead of failing fast</summary>
